---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Navbar from '../components/Navbar.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const lastUpdated = 'June 9, 2026';

const sections = [
  {
    id: 'who-we-are',
    title: 'Who We Are',
    content: `HeyView is an independent design and AI studio operated by Tojii Company SRL, a company registered in Costa Rica. We work with businesses that run on complex operations — helping them design systems, automations, and digital experiences that make their work sharper and easier to scale.

This Privacy Policy describes how we collect, use, and protect information when you visit our website (heyview.studio) or interact with us.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'information-we-collect',
    title: 'Information We Collect',
    content: `We collect only the information necessary to communicate with prospective clients and deliver our services.

**Information you provide directly:**
When you book a discovery call through Cal.com, you share your name, email address, and any details you include in the booking form. We receive this information to prepare for and conduct our meeting.

**Information collected automatically:**
When you visit our website, we use PostHog — a third-party analytics service — to collect data about how visitors interact with the site. This includes pages visited, time spent, clicks, and session duration. PostHog assigns a unique identifier to your browser using a cookie so we can understand returning visits and aggregate usage patterns. This data is processed on PostHog's servers in the United States.

**Information from third-party services:**
Our website loads icon fonts from Google's servers (Material Symbols). This means Google receives a request from your browser, which may include your IP address and browser information, subject to Google's own privacy policy.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'how-we-use-it',
    title: 'How We Use Your Information',
    content: `We use the information we collect to:

- Respond to your inquiry and schedule discovery calls
- Assess whether there is a mutual fit for working together
- Deliver services to active clients
- Send project-related communications during an engagement

We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes. We do not send unsolicited emails or newsletters unless you have explicitly opted in.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'cookies',
    title: 'Cookies & Tracking',
    content: `Our website uses PostHog for analytics. PostHog sets a first-party cookie (prefixed \`ph_\`) to identify your browser session across visits. This helps us understand which pages are most useful and where the site can be improved. PostHog does not use this data to build ad profiles or track you across unrelated websites.

Cal.com, our scheduling provider, may also set cookies when you interact with the booking widget. These are governed by Cal.com's own privacy policy.

If you prefer not to be tracked, you can block analytics cookies through your browser settings or a content blocker. You can also contact us directly at privacy@heyview.studio if you have questions about opting out.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'third-party-services',
    title: 'Third-Party Services',
    content: `We use the following third-party services on this website:

**Cal.com** — appointment scheduling. When you book a call, your name, email, and meeting details are processed by Cal.com. Their privacy policy applies to that data.

**PostHog** — website analytics. PostHog collects behavioral data about site visits (page views, clicks, session duration) and processes it on servers in the United States. You can review their privacy policy at posthog.com/privacy.

**Google Fonts / Material Symbols** — icon rendering. Loading these resources sends a network request to Google's CDN, subject to Google's privacy policy.

We are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party services and encourage you to review their respective policies.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'data-security',
    title: 'Data Security',
    content: `We take reasonable technical and organizational measures to protect your personal information from unauthorized access, loss, or misuse. Our website is served over HTTPS. Communication with prospective and active clients occurs over encrypted channels.

No method of transmission over the internet is 100% secure. While we do our best to protect your data, we cannot guarantee absolute security.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'data-retention',
    title: 'Data Retention',
    content: `We retain contact and project-related information for as long as necessary to manage our business relationship and comply with legal obligations. If you would like us to delete your data, you may request this at any time by contacting us at privacy@heyview.studio, and we will respond within 30 days.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'your-rights',
    title: 'Your Rights',
    content: `Under Costa Rica's Ley de Protección de la Persona frente al Tratamiento de sus Datos Personales (Ley 8968), you have the right to:

- Know what personal data we hold about you
- Correct inaccurate or incomplete data
- Request deletion of your data
- Withdraw consent for processing, where consent was the legal basis

To exercise any of these rights, contact us at privacy@heyview.studio. We will acknowledge your request within 5 business days and resolve it within 30 days.

If you are located in the European Union or United Kingdom, you may have additional rights under GDPR or UK GDPR. We honor the same principles of transparency, access, and erasure regardless of your location.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'changes',
    title: 'Changes to This Policy',
    content: `We may update this policy as our services evolve or to reflect changes in applicable law. When we do, we will update the "Last updated" date at the top of this page. We encourage you to review this policy periodically. Continued use of the website after changes are posted constitutes acceptance of the updated policy.`,
  },
  {
    id: 'contact',
    title: 'Contact Us',
    content: `If you have questions or concerns about this Privacy Policy or how we handle your data, please reach out:

**HeyView** (operated by Tojii Company SRL)
San José, Costa Rica

Email: privacy@heyview.studio`,
  },
];
---

<Layout
  title="Privacy Policy — HeyView"
  description="HeyView's privacy policy: how we collect, use, and protect your information."
>
  <div class="max-w-360 mx-auto relative shadow-sm">
    <Navbar transition:persist />

    <main id="main-content">

      <!-- Page header -->
      <section class="bg-cream px-5 md:px-16 pt-20 pb-16" style="border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--color-cream-border);">
        <span class="eyebrow text-navy/50 block mb-6">Legal</span>
        <h1 class="font-serif text-[40px] md:text-[56px] font-normal text-navy leading-tight mb-4">
          Privacy Policy
        </h1>
        <p class="font-sans text-[13px]" style="color: rgba(30, 42, 56, 0.5);">
          Last updated: {lastUpdated}
        </p>
      </section>

      <!-- Policy body -->
      <section class="bg-cream px-5 md:px-16 py-20">
        <div class="max-w-2xl">

          <!-- Intro blurb -->
          <p class="font-sans text-[17px] leading-relaxed mb-16" style="color: rgba(30, 42, 56, 0.8);">
            We keep this policy short and plain. HeyView is a small studio — we collect only what we need, we don't sell anything, and we treat your information with the same discretion we'd expect in return.
          </p>

          <!-- Table of contents -->
          <nav aria-label="Policy sections" class="mb-16 p-8" style="border: 0.5px solid var(--color-cream-border);">
            <p class="eyebrow text-navy/50 mb-5">Contents</p>
            <ol class="flex flex-col gap-2">
              {sections.map((section, i) => (
                <li>
                  <a
                    href={`#${section.id}`}
                    class="font-sans text-[14px] font-medium text-navy/70 hover:text-navy transition-colors"
                  >
                    <span class="font-mono text-accent mr-2" style="font-size: 11px;">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
                    {section.title}
                  </a>
                </li>
              ))}
            </ol>
          </nav>

          <!-- Sections -->
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-16">
            {sections.map((section, i) => (
              <article id={section.id} class="scroll-mt-24">
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-4 mb-6" style="border-bottom: 0.5px solid var(--color-cream-border); padding-bottom: 1rem;">
                  <span class="font-sans text-[11px] font-mono" style="color: #A87C52;">{String(i + 1).padStart(2, '0')}</span>
                  <h2 class="font-serif text-[22px] text-navy font-medium">{section.title}</h2>
                </div>
                <div class="font-sans text-[17px] leading-relaxed policy-content" style="color: rgba(30, 42, 56, 0.82);">
                  {section.content.split('\n\n').map((para) => {
                    if (para.startsWith('**') && para.endsWith('**') === false && para.includes('**\n')) {
                      // bold label + indented list — handled below
                    }
                    return <p class="mb-4 last:mb-0" set:html={para
                      .replace(/\*\*(.*?)\*\*/g, '<strong>$1</strong>')
                      .replace(/\n- /g, '<br/>• ')
                      .replace(/^- /, '• ')
                    } />;
                  })}
                </div>
              </article>
            ))}
          </div>

        </div>
      </section>

    </main>

    <Footer />
  </div>
</Layout>

<style>
  .policy-content strong {
    color: #1E2A38;
    font-weight: 600;
  }
</style>
